    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-120 is a single chain recombinant human peptide produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized to be identical to the human gene which codes for E2F Transcription Factor 4 used such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 413 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
